%% Service call sequence — asynchronous order production over RabbitMQ. Render at https://mermaid.live
sequenceDiagram
    actor S as Shop Staff
    participant API as PrintHub.Api
    participant DB as SQL Server
    participant MQ as RabbitMQ
    participant PA as ProductionAgent

    S->>API: PUT /api/orders/{id}/start (assign machine)
    API->>DB: order -> InProduction, machine -> Busy
    API->>MQ: publish job.dispatch (orderId, items, machine)
    MQ->>PA: deliver production job
    loop while producing
        PA->>MQ: publish job.progress (percent)
        MQ->>API: progress event (consumer)
        API->>DB: update ProgressPercent
    end
    alt produced successfully
        PA->>MQ: publish job.completed
        MQ->>API: completion event
        API->>DB: order -> ReadyForPickup, machine -> Idle
    else machine fault
        PA->>MQ: publish job.failed (reason)
        MQ->>API: failure event
        API->>DB: order -> ProductionFailed
    end
    Note over MQ,PA: retries + dead-letter queue, idempotent handlers ignore duplicate events
